cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DS

The paper discusses networks with wireless devices and communication channels, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The focus on spatial aspects of the network, such as node distribution and distance-dependent link probability, suggests a possible sub-category of spatial networks (cs.SI). The consideration of interference and directivity in wireless communication suggests a possible sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of geometry, including convex, non-convex, and fractal shapes, suggests a possible sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the consideration of mobility suggests a possible sub-category of distributed systems (cs.DS).
